<br/>
<div class="phototagleft">
Photo by Rafael Trindade
</div>
</div>
<p style="margin-bottom:16px"><strong><a href="https://mariaelenamoran.com/">María Elena Morán</a></strong> (b. 1985, Maracaibo) is a Venezuelan writer and screenwriter based in Brazil. She has a degree in journalism from the Universidad del Zulia, studied screenwriting at the EICTV in Cuba, and holds a PhD in creative writing from the Pontifícia Universidade Católica do Rio Grande do Sul. She is the author of the novel <em>Los Continentes del Adentro</em>, and her second novel, <em>Volver a cuándo</em>, will be published in English by Knopf in 2026.</p>
<div class="clear"></div>
<div class="imageleft">
<img src="/sites/worldliteraturetoday.org/files/madeline_jones-b.jpg" alt width="150" height="150" border="1" />
<br/>
<div class="phototagleft">
</div>
</div>
<p style="margin-bottom:16px"><strong><a href="https://reedsy.com/madeline-jones">Madeline Jones</a></strong> (@MadelineCJones) is a literary translator and book editor at Algonquin Books. She is currently completing a master’s degree in translation studies at the Universitat Pompeu Fabra and lives between Barcelona and New York. Her first book-length translation, María Elena Morán's <em>Volver a cuándo</em>, is forthcoming from Knopf.</p>
